definitionGroups.group: (of a person or enterprise) having been issued with a licence (by the required authority)

entries.meaning: (of a shop or restaurant) allowed to sell alcohol
examples: The opening hours of licensed premises are restricted to prevent all-night drinking.

entries.meaning: (of a product) based on an existing piece of intellectual property and sold under licence.
examples: Although they sell well, licensed video games are seldom critically acclaimed.

entries.meaning: simple past tense and past participle of license
